ongs, this book is a work of implicit patriotism and creative skepticism. It illuminates Dylan’s continuing presence and relevance through his empathy—his imaginative identification with other people. This is not only a deeply felt telling of the life and times of Bob Dylan, but a rich history of American folk songs and the new life they were given as Dylan sat down to write his own.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aComposerszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aSingerszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Composers & Musicians.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073923740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300268829?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300268829423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300268829/original  a978-3-11-073923-7  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY